<h2>Attacking</h2>

<p>There are three types of attacks you can launch against other empires.</p>

<h4>Army Attack</h4>
<p>
  Send soldiers to attack another empire. You choose how many of each unit type to send,
  whether to use wine for a morale boost, and the attack objective.
</p>

<p><strong>Attack objectives:</strong></p>
<table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
  <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Effect</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><strong>Conquer</strong></td><td>Take land from the defender based on units sent</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Raid</strong></td><td>Deal light damage to resources (low loss scale ~10%)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Rob</strong></td><td>Steal resources with moderate damage (scale ~50%)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Slaughter</strong></td><td>Kill population and army with heavy damage (scale ~50%)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Wine boost:</strong> Sending 1 wine per soldier boosts attack power proportionally to your wine stock relative to army size.</p>

<p><strong>Attack cost:</strong> Food and gold are consumed during the campaign (approximately 6 turns worth of upkeep per soldier).</p>

<h4>Score Ratio Penalties</h4>
<p>
  Attacking a player much weaker than you carries significant penalties.
  The ratio is attacker score ÷ defender score:
</p>
<table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th class="text-center">Score Ratio</th>
      <th class="text-center">Run Chance</th>
      <th class="text-center">Victory Points</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td class="text-center">Below 2×</td><td class="text-center">0%</td><td class="text-center">100%</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="text-center">2×</td><td class="text-center">20%</td><td class="text-center">50%</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="text-center">3×</td><td class="text-center">30%</td><td class="text-center">40%</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="text-center">4×</td><td class="text-center">40%</td><td class="text-center">30%</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="text-center">5×</td><td class="text-center">50%</td><td class="text-center">20%</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="text-center">6×</td><td class="text-center">60%</td><td class="text-center">10%</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="text-center">8×</td><td class="text-center">70%</td><td class="text-center">5%</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="text-center">10× or more</td><td class="text-center">80%</td><td class="text-center">1%</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

